WEBVTT

00:00.776 --> 00:02.410
<i>Previously on "Heartland":</i>

00:02.477 --> 00:03.977
H'yah!

00:05.814 --> 00:08.048
- Dad!
- Are you okay?

00:08.116 --> 00:11.118
Strained a few ligaments.
No tears this time.

00:11.186 --> 00:12.754
There are very few girls

00:12.821 --> 00:14.988
that I feel like
I can be myself around.

00:15.055 --> 00:16.222
We're pals.

00:16.291 --> 00:18.925
You know,
really good friends.

00:19.827 --> 00:22.061
Your dad isn't Charlie Wells,
is he?

00:22.129 --> 00:23.430
<i>Your demo?</i>

00:23.498 --> 00:26.366
Uh, I could give it
to him for you.

00:26.434 --> 00:27.867
Really?

00:27.935 --> 00:29.568
Well, Lou and I are thinking
about building our own place.

00:29.636 --> 00:32.505
A new baby,
a huge do-it-yourself project,

00:32.572 --> 00:34.573
a wife with extremely
high expectations...

00:34.641 --> 00:36.375
What could possibly
go wrong?

00:36.443 --> 00:39.679
As your honorary grandma,

00:39.746 --> 00:42.348
I would be proud
to pay for your education.

00:42.416 --> 00:44.283
There's no point
socking it all way.

00:45.884 --> 00:47.118
<i>Well, are you
sure you don't mind</i>

00:47.186 --> 00:48.453
<i>coming all the way
out here?</i>

00:48.521 --> 00:50.488
It's a bit of drive.

00:50.556 --> 00:52.457
Honey, come take a look
at this.

00:52.525 --> 00:54.192
Okay. All right.
Well...

00:54.259 --> 00:56.093
I can't wait to catch up
with you.

00:56.161 --> 00:57.495
All right.

00:57.563 --> 00:58.830
Yes?

00:58.897 --> 01:01.699
Uh... so,
what do you like better:

01:01.766 --> 01:05.035
Kitchen, separate dining room, or...

01:05.102 --> 01:06.303
More of an open concept?

01:06.371 --> 01:07.904
Mm-hm.

01:07.972 --> 01:10.006
Um... I don't know.

01:10.074 --> 01:12.676
You know, it's kind of...
It's hard to visualize.

01:12.744 --> 01:13.910
Right.

01:13.978 --> 01:15.045
It might be a little easier
to visualize

01:15.112 --> 01:16.279
if you weren't on the phone
all the time.

01:16.348 --> 01:17.513
I'm sorry.

01:17.581 --> 01:18.748
An old friend
from New York called.

01:18.816 --> 01:19.982
He's in town
for a few days,

01:20.050 --> 01:22.218
so we set up
a lunch date.

01:22.285 --> 01:25.120
A lunch date?
Should I be jealous?

01:25.188 --> 01:26.922
Only of his exceptional
taste in clothes

01:26.990 --> 01:29.592
and his collection
of rare orchids.

01:29.660 --> 01:31.361
Anyway, do you mind
if I disappear

01:31.428 --> 01:33.229
for a few hours
this afternoon?

01:33.296 --> 01:35.196
- On one condition.
- What?

01:35.264 --> 01:37.432
Open concept,
or separate dining room?

01:37.500 --> 01:39.801
Ugh! Okay...

01:39.869 --> 01:41.503
Open concept.

01:41.571 --> 01:43.772
Mm... no. Wait.
Separate dining room.

01:43.840 --> 01:44.906
Definitely
a separate dining room.

01:44.974 --> 01:45.907
Okay.

01:45.975 --> 01:48.309
No. Open concept,
I think.

01:48.378 --> 01:49.844
I love you.

01:53.114 --> 01:54.348
<i>Ty!</i>

01:57.619 --> 01:59.319
Aw, you shouldn't have.

01:59.388 --> 02:00.588
I'm sorry.

02:00.655 --> 02:02.155
These are for the "other woman"
in my life.

02:02.223 --> 02:03.424
Mrs. Bell.
Oh.

02:03.492 --> 02:04.725
Hey, Mallory.

02:04.793 --> 02:05.759
I gotta run.
I have go talk to Austin

02:05.826 --> 02:07.126
before his shift ends.

02:07.194 --> 02:08.527
Austin.
What happened to Jake?

02:08.596 --> 02:09.795
Me and Jake are
just friends now.

02:09.864 --> 02:11.030
Try and keep up.

02:11.098 --> 02:12.164
Yeah!

02:13.100 --> 02:14.701
So what's the occasion?

02:14.769 --> 02:15.869
Well, I called
the university

02:15.936 --> 02:17.236
to work out
a payment schedule,

02:17.304 --> 02:19.506
but it turns out
my tuition's been covered.

02:19.573 --> 02:20.740
Really.

02:20.808 --> 02:21.940
Mrs. Bell came through
for you.

02:22.008 --> 02:23.442
Yeah. And I'm gonna
pay her back eventually,

02:23.510 --> 02:25.210
but, for now,
the flowers will have to do.

02:25.278 --> 02:26.812
All right. Well, you tell her
I say hi, huh?

02:26.880 --> 02:28.680
- I will. See ya
-  'Kay. Bye.

02:31.418 --> 02:33.719
So, uh,
what're you doing tomorrow?

02:33.787 --> 02:35.320
Nothing...

02:35.388 --> 02:37.255
If you consider yard work,

02:37.323 --> 02:38.623
hanging out with dozens
of friends

02:38.690 --> 02:41.726
and babysitting "nothing."

02:41.794 --> 02:43.428
'Cause I got the day
off work tomorrow

02:43.495 --> 02:46.831
and I was wondering
do you wanna hang out?

02:46.899 --> 02:50.301
I guess I could
squeeze you in.

02:50.368 --> 02:53.137
I'm glad you're here.
I wanted to tell you something.

02:53.204 --> 02:54.337
You know that guy
I told you about,

02:54.405 --> 02:55.672
the one I met in London?

02:55.740 --> 02:57.040
Yeah...

02:57.107 --> 03:00.176
Well, I didn't exactly
tell you the whole story.

03:00.244 --> 03:01.545
It was prince Harry,
wasn't it?

03:01.612 --> 03:04.848
No. His name is Dillon
and he's from Toronto,

03:04.916 --> 03:06.516
but he's over there
going to school.

03:06.584 --> 03:09.518
And I know I told you
nothing happened,

03:09.586 --> 03:11.386
but...
But something happened?

03:11.455 --> 03:12.521
No.

03:13.690 --> 03:15.891
Yes. I...
I don't know.

03:15.959 --> 03:18.026
He sent me this text.

03:18.094 --> 03:19.227
"I miss you.

03:19.295 --> 03:20.563
I can't stop thinking
about you."

03:20.630 --> 03:22.331
Soraya,
this is adorable.

03:22.398 --> 03:24.099
Adorable?
It's not adorable.

03:24.167 --> 03:25.233
It's crazy.

03:25.301 --> 03:26.568
I knew this guy
all of two weeks.

03:26.635 --> 03:28.603
Well, you obviously left
quite the impression.

03:28.671 --> 03:30.071
I already made a mistake
with Chase.

03:30.138 --> 03:31.473
I don't wanna make
another one

03:31.540 --> 03:34.476
with a guy that doesn't even
live in the country.

03:34.543 --> 03:36.778
So what're you gonna do?

03:36.846 --> 03:38.947
I'm gonna ignore the text.

03:40.282 --> 03:42.483
I need a milkshake.

